---
import { PLATFORM_DESCRIPTION, PLATFORM_NAME } from "astro:env/client";
import ArticleLayout from "#src/layouts/Article.astro";
---

<ArticleLayout>
  <hgroup class="page-title-group">
    <h1 class="page-title">About {PLATFORM_NAME}</h1>
    <p class="page-description">{PLATFORM_DESCRIPTION}</p>
  </hgroup>

  <p>
    <strong>{PLATFORM_NAME}</strong> was created by <a href="https://ssbit01.github.io" target="_blank">Stefan Samson (SSbit01)</a> as an alternative
    to platforms like <a href="https://linktr.ee" target="_blank">Linktree</a>. It aims to provide a simpler, more focused way to create
    micropages and profiles, through links and markdown text.
  </p>

  <section>
    <h2>The Mission</h2>
    <p>
      In an increasingly fragmented digital world, <strong>{PLATFORM_NAME}</strong> was built with three core principles in mind:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>User Privacy:</strong> it don't track you or your visitors.</li>
      <li><strong>Simplicity:</strong> No bloat, no unnecessary features, just your content.</li>
      <li><strong>Ownership:</strong> Your profile, your content, your business.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>No Tracking, No Data Collection</h2>
    <p>
      Privacy isn't just a feature. it's a foundation. Visitors to any <strong>{PLATFORM_NAME}</strong> profile can browse with confidence, knowing
      that their activity is never tracked. <strong>{PLATFORM_NAME}</strong> does not set advertising or analytics cookies, and your data is <strong
        >never sold or shared</strong
      > with third parties.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Open to the Community</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>{PLATFORM_NAME}</strong> is built using modern open-source technologies. The goal is to grow alongside users, building the features
      that actually matter to you.
    </p>
  </section>
</ArticleLayout>

<style lang="scss">
  .page-title-group {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color) 0%, var(--color-highlight) 100%);
    background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; // It works in Firefox too.
    margin-block-end: 2rem;
  }

  .page-title {
    margin-block-end: 0;
  }

  .page-description {
    margin-block-start: 0;
    font-size: clamp(1em, 4.5vw, 1.25em);
    text-align: center;
  }

  section {
    margin-block: 2.5rem;
    h2 {
      margin-block-end: 1rem;
      color: var(--color-highlight);
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
